name: Little Water Cantina
description: Little Water Cantina was built to LEED platinum standards which makes it one of the "greenest" restaurants in the country. It serves both traditional and original Mexican dishes using as many local and organic ingredients as possible. Freshly squeezed lime margaritas, ceviches using local seafood and tacos, burritos & chimichangas! Located in Seattle's cozy Eastlake neighborhood, Little Water has a 2,200 square foot patio that looks out to Lake Union, Gas Works Park and the Olympic Mountains. A portion of our patio is enclosed and heated during the colder months; when the weather permits, our patio bar can be reserved for groups of up to 30 people.

Spirits Unleashed: Ghost Hunting and Booze at Pike Place Market

name: Spirits Unleashed: Ghost Hunting and Booze at Pike Place Market
description:
Learn about Pike Place Markets spooky side on this ghost tour. Follow a guide on a walk the market, including sites such as the underground market, an Irish Pub in an ancient mortuary, and dark hallways, all while listening to market lore. This ghost tour is a fun introduction to the market and spirits history. Speaking of spirits, your guide will be buying you some along the way.

Thoughtful Chef Tours is permitted and licensed by the Pike Place Market Preservation and Development Authority (PDA) to operate in the Pike Place market Historical District. The PDA requires any business or person conducting paid tours within its properties and in the public areas of the historical district to be pre-approved and to have a license for this activity.

review.name: A wonderful guide!
review.reviewBody: My bridesmaids, husband, and I ghost tour with Carolyn last week. We had an amazing time! Carolyn is so thoughtful and warm, and she's quick and great at adapting when things don't go as planned. We were all impressed by the research she'd done - even my know-it-all PhD candidate twin! I'd love to do another tour with her. She's a James Beard chef and I think it would be wonderful to do one of her food-related tours, too.

review.name: Great way to end our trip!
review.reviewBody: Katherine was amazing and so charismatic ! So much history and she made visiting pike place market even more amazing! Letting us know about the new speakeasy Karoo after the tour was an highlight and the drinks are awesome! Highly recommend the midnight mumba!

review.name: Happy Hour with Spirits of more than one kind
review.reviewBody: I was looking for something a little out of the ordinary to do for a couple of hours on a Friday evening in Seattle, and Carolyn's ghost hunting + drinks tour at Pike Place Market fit the bill perfectly.  The stories were fascinating, the drinks were quite all right, and the company was terrific.  To really get the most out of this experience, it helps to come with a completely open mind and an interest in local history.  If that's your roll, you'll have a great time.

review.name: A wonderfully spooky night!
review.reviewBody: I had an amazing night with my boyfriend on Chef Carolyn’s ghost hunting tour! She is a wealth of information, and provided an insightful look onto the history of the market and the establishments that reside in the market. The drink selection was also a nice addition to this spooky tour. If you want a fun night walking around with ghost hunting gear in a historic area, this is the tour for you!

review.name: Fantastic tour! Cool bars, spooky stories!
review.reviewBody: We had a great time! The bars were cool and the stories were even cooler. We felt connected to Seattle after the tour and it made the rest of our trip  that much intense.

review.name: Such a wonderful experience
review.reviewBody: Carolyn was awesome! Our tour ended up just being my boyfriend and I, and it turned out to be wonderful. She is very knowledgeable of the spirits and the history of Seattle. Not to mention a very sweet and upbeat woman. I would take this again in a heartbeat.

review.name: Not what I thought
review.reviewBody: We stopped at three bars. We were at the first bar for an hour. Everyone was asking why we were still there. There was no walking through pike place. There was maybe 2 ghost stories and the guide couldn’t keep them straight. I’ve never done an event that was so off from what I was expecting.

review.name: Highly would recommend
review.reviewBody: It was a great experience getting to know the market place a little more. Would highly recommend For tourists!

review.name: Amazing host and amazing spots!
review.reviewBody: Carolyn is amazing! I couldn’t recommend this enough. She’s so warm and welcoming and it’s the only tour that includes drinks!

review.name: Learned alot of history.
review.reviewBody:
Book as many tours as you can. You're going to have a great time.
There are alot of floors underground that are filled with shops. Wish we had more time to spend exploring the underground.

itemListElement.name: Savor the Sea: Guided Seafood Tasting at Pike Place Ma

name: Savor the Sea: Guided Seafood Tasting at Pike Place Ma
description: Pike Place Market is famous for fish flying thru the air and fresh seafood. Enjoy a walking tour that includes seafood tastings and market stories told by a professional storyteller. Enjoy salmon, dungeness crab, clam chowder, shrimp ceviche, shrimp cocktail, sushi grade fish and salmon jerky.

review.name: A Must Have
review.reviewBody: Thoughtful Chef Tours owner and tour guide was phenomenal yesterday at showing us the seafood scene at the Pike Place Market! Her demeanor and personality are so disarming and pleasant toward participants, vendors and most notably “competing” tour guides  companies. This said a lot about her personally and professionally. Her stories about the market history were conveyed in a very digestible way and a lot of the tidbits shared highlighted the historical self sufficiency of Seattle. Having been a chef, Carolyn’s seafood choices were phenomenal, especially the clam chowder! Holy cow that was THEE BEST EVER. The portions supplied in the samples were surprisingly filling. Seriously, I’d recommend EVERYONE coming to Seattle to sign up with Carolyn at Thoughful Chef Tours. It’d be a decision you won’t regret!

review.name: Great food tour!
review.reviewBody:
What a great tour !
Carolyn has selected some of the best foodie spots in Pike Place Market. Amazing knowledge of the vendors on how they source and sell the products .
The historical side of the tour was extremely interesting as well. 
Great time spent with a lovely lady.
Nigel & Caz

review.name: Wonderful tour and amazing food.
review.reviewBody:
The tour was fabulous! I have been to Pikes Place Market at least 8 times in my life but still learned so much about the market, its vendors and, its history. 
Our guide was so knowledgeable and friendly with all the vendors and the rest of the tour attendees. We all had a great time. 

I HIGHLY recommend this tour, you will not be disappointed.

review.name: Wonderful history and a seafood lover's dream tour
review.reviewBody: Our guide was fantastic...I'm a Seattle resident of 35 years, and I learned so much history about the origins of this wonderful Town that I hadn't heard before. And the quality and amount of establishments we visited gave us a really tasty 😋 overview of the incredible seafood our Salish sea has to offer us.

review.name: Fab experience with Carolyn
review.reviewBody: Fab experience with Carolyn on the Pike Place Savor the Sea Tour. Such a detailed history and authentic stories make this a one of a kind. You will leave with a full belly and happy heart. She not only takes you to wonderful choices at the Market, she speaks of the community feel and family owned business stories.

review.name: Well worth the time! Great tour guide!
review.reviewBody:
Chef Carolyn is an amazing tour guide!

She not only took us through the notable spots of Pike Place Market, but was able to field even some off the cuff questions that came up.

Make sure you sign up for her tour when you come to Seattle.

review.name: Seattle SideTrip
review.reviewBody: My hubby and I enjoyed the delectable bites and savory samples. Our favorites included the Clam Chowder, Salmon Jerky and Smoked Salmon. The Cod Stew was like a Tomato-Based Gumbo. Chef Carolyn added tidbits of History and local lore to our experience. She also gave us directions back to vendors who peaked our interests along the tour.

review.name: A must to do
review.reviewBody: Carolyn did not only take us on a seafood tasting tour, she also gave us the history Pike Place.  She is an accredited chef, so don't be afraid to ask questions.   You will taste salmon, shrimp, oysters, crab and the yummy clam chowder. You will see flying fish (but not their own) .  There is walking involved.  Check out where're 2 elevators are.  One is the sky bridge, leaving only 1 hill to climb.  Don't miss the opportunity to take this tour.

review.name: A memorable seafood tour with a true foodie!
review.reviewBody:
Touring the iconic Pike Place Market with Carolyn (aka The Thoughtful Chef) was a true delight! She had a great personality and her love of food was infectious to us all! 
Everyone in the market knew her so we felt we got VIP attention at every stall or business we visited. 

This wasn't just a food tour; it was general education too on so much about Seattle! We got lessons in history, geology, culture, events...and left smarter than when we arrived. 

This was a great experience with all types of seafood. We got to do the iconic things like watching the throwing fish, but importantly, we tasted everything from oysters, crab, cod and different types of salmon to seafood chowder, salmon jerky and shrimp cocktail. 

We also got little insider tips on the market and sampled other items too like homemade cookies. This was a memorable tour that will stay with us for a long time to come! Highly recommend it if you've got a few hours to spare and love seafood! 

We were totally stuffed by the time we were done and didn't need to get dinner afterward, so doing this tour saved us money on both lunch and dinner too! :-)

review.name: Awesome and Them Some
review.reviewBody:
Carolyn was fantastic!  I loved this tour and I don’t even like fish! 😂😂😂 

She is extremely knowledgeable about where to find the best “of the best at Pike’s Place”Market and then enhances the tour with her knowledge of the history of Seattle.  You can’t go wrong with this tour!
